{
  format: 1
  name: json-array-shorter-prefix-sorts-first
  suite: scenario
  spec: ["#annex-b", "§B.3"]
  tags: ["ordering", "json"]
  note: '''
    §B.3 array order: "lexicographic element order; shorter array first after a
    shared prefix", and numbers use "mathematical numeric order". Two traps:
      1. Length: after a shared prefix the shorter array precedes the longer
         one ([1,2] < [1,2,3]), but a mismatch inside the prefix decides first
         regardless of length ([1,2,3] < [1,3] because element 1: 2 < 3).
      2. Numeric elements compare mathematically, not textually: [1,2] < [1,10]
         because 2 < 10. A per-character/text sorter would place [1,10] before
         [1,2].
    Correct ascending order of the seeded arrays:
      [1] < [1,2] < [1,2,3] < [1,3] < [1,10] < [2]
  '''

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.annexb.jsonarr@1.0.0"
    $model: {
      rows: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "text"
        a: "json"
      }
      $public: {
        by_a: { $view: ".rows { id, a, $sort: [a] }" }
      }
    }
    $data: {
      rows: {
        r5: { a: [1, 10] }
        r1: { a: [1] }
        r3: { a: [1, 2, 3] }
        r6: { a: [2] }
        r2: { a: [1, 2] }
        r4: { a: [1, 3] }
      }
    }
  }

  steps: [
    { watch: "public.by_a", id: "w1",
      expect_init: { value: [
        { id: "r1", a: [1] }
        { id: "r2", a: [1, 2] }
        { id: "r3", a: [1, 2, 3] }
        { id: "r4", a: [1, 3] }
        { id: "r5", a: [1, 10] }
        { id: "r6", a: [2] }
      ] } }
  ]
}
